title: Guineans Vote in Second-Ever Free Election
text:
Voters in Guinea, the West African nation still recovering from the worst Ebola epidemic in history, lined up in the rain on Sunday to take part in their countryâ€™s second-ever free election.
Booths opened flanked by anti-riot police, while hospitals were still treating the scores injured when police broke up anti-incumbent protests over the last few days. Jingles on the radio prayed for a peaceful vote.
